commit.message: Make output consistently key:value, for better machine readability.
Print version table regardless of provisioning status.

Merge pull request #9 from ivan-m/patch-1

Make what to do a bit more obvious

Merge pull request #10 from chneukirchen/master

Remove direct inclusion of <bits/wordsize.h>

Remove direct inclusion of <bits/wordsize.h>

This allows building on non-glibc systems such as musl, and wordsize.h
is included via stdint.h anyway.

Make what to do a bit more obvious

To avoid confusion from people trying to work out how to test their systems: https://lists.samba.org/archive/linux/2017-May/036104.html

Clarify things further

This message could be misinterpeted, so add some more detail.

Explicitly include sys/time.h

https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=14335661 suggests that this might be
necessary on some systems.

Clarify output

Make some of the output messages a little clearer

Check for MEI interface at both /dev/mei0 and /dev/mei.

Check for MEI interface at both /dev/mei0 and /dev/mei.

Also, make sure that an error on open (e.g., EPERM if not run as root)
is reported with the /dev filename that we actually tried.
